<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#add8ff" WIDTH="150"><B>Analysis</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">The controlling factor which we have<BR ALIGN='left'/>concluded brings this case within the<BR ALIGN='left'/>statute is that a basic element of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>plan was the continuance of the chemical<BR ALIGN='left'/>manufacturing business in the corporate<BR ALIGN='left'/>shell of the new company, with the gain<BR ALIGN='left'/>(were it not for the &quot;boot&quot;) not having<BR ALIGN='left'/>sufficiently crystallized for<BR ALIGN='left'/>recognition, because the collective<BR ALIGN='left'/>interests of the shareholders &quot;still<BR ALIGN='left'/>remained in solution.&quot;</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
