<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#b6e3b6" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">As a leading practitioner has put it,<BR ALIGN='left'/>&quot;the essence of [a statutory<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganization] is a continuance of the<BR ALIGN='left'/>proprietary interests in the continuing<BR ALIGN='left'/>enterprise under modified corporate<BR ALIGN='left'/>form, the transaction being deemed<BR ALIGN='left'/>insufficiently closed economically to<BR ALIGN='left'/>justify a tax at the time, except in so<BR ALIGN='left'/>far as the stockholder gets something in<BR ALIGN='left'/>addition to stock or securities in the<BR ALIGN='left'/>reorganized company.&quot;</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
